verses.text_plain: Keep not thou silence, O God: hold not thy peace, and be not still, O God.
verses.verse_html:
1Keep not thou silence, O God: hold not thy peace, and be not still, O God. ▼
▼ of Asaph: or, for Asaph

footnotes.body_html: ▼ of Asaph: or, for Asaph

verses.text_plain: For, lo, thine enemies make a tumult: and they that hate thee have lifted up the head.
verses.verse_html: 2For, lo, thine enemies make a tumult: and they that hate thee have lifted up the head.

verses.text_plain: They have taken crafty counsel against thy people, and consulted against thy hidden ones.
verses.verse_html: 3They have taken crafty counsel against thy people, and consulted against thy hidden ones.

verses.text_plain: They have said, Come, and let us cut them off from being a nation; that the name of Israel may be no more in remembrance.
verses.verse_html: 4They have said, Come, and let us cut them off from being a nation; that the name of Israel may be no more in remembrance.

tokens.text: and let us cut them off
may be no more in remembrance

verses.text_plain: For they have consulted together with one consent: they are confederate against thee:
verses.verse_html:
5For they have consulted together with one consent: they are confederate against thee: ▼
▼ consent: Heb. heart

verses.text_plain: The tabernacles of Edom, and the Ishmaelites; of Moab, and the Hagarenes;
verses.verse_html: 6The tabernacles of Edom, and the Ishmaelites; of Moab, and the Hagarenes;

verses.text_plain: Gebal, and Ammon, and Amalek; the Philistines with the inhabitants of Tyre;
verses.verse_html: 7Gebal, and Ammon, and Amalek; the Philistines with the inhabitants of Tyre;

verses.text_plain: Assur also is joined with them: they have holpen the children of Lot. Selah.
verses.verse_html:
8Assur also is joined with them: they have holpen the children of Lot. Selah. ▼
▼ holpen: Heb. been an arm to

footnotes.body_text: ▼ holpen: Heb. been an arm to
footnotes.body_html: ▼ holpen: Heb. been an arm to

verses.text_plain: Do unto them as unto the Midianites; as to Sisera, as to Jabin, at the brook of Kison:
verses.verse_html: 9Do unto them as unto the Midianites; as to Sisera, as to Jabin, at the brook of Kison:

verses.text_plain: Which perished at En–dor: they became as dung for the earth.
verses.verse_html: 10Which perished at En–dor: they became as dung for the earth.

verses.text_plain: Make their nobles like Oreb, and like Zeeb: yea, all their princes as Zebah, and as Zalmunna:
verses.verse_html: 11Make their nobles like Oreb, and like Zeeb: yea, all their princes as Zebah, and as Zalmunna:

verses.text_plain: Who said, Let us take to ourselves the houses of God in possession.
verses.verse_html: 12Who said, Let us take to ourselves the houses of God in possession.

tokens.text: Let us take to ourselves the houses

verses.text_plain: O my God, make them like a wheel; as the stubble before the wind.
verses.verse_html: 13O my God, make them like a wheel; as the stubble before the wind.

verses.text_plain: As the fire burneth a wood, and as the flame setteth the mountains on fire;
verses.verse_html: 14As the fire burneth a wood, and as the flame setteth the mountains on fire;

verses.text_plain: So persecute them with thy tempest, and make them afraid with thy storm.
verses.verse_html: 15So persecute them with thy tempest, and make them afraid with thy storm.

verses.text_plain: Fill their faces with shame; that they may seek thy name, O Lord.
verses.verse_html: 16Fill their faces with shame; that they may seek thy name, O Lord.

verses.text_plain: Let them be confounded and troubled for ever; yea, let them be put to shame, and perish:
verses.verse_html: 17Let them be confounded and troubled for ever; yea, let them be put to shame, and perish:

tokens.text: yea, let them be put to shame

verses.text_plain: That men may know that thou, whose name alone is Jehovah, art the most high over all the earth.
verses.verse_html: 18That men may know that thou, whose name alone is Jehovah, art the most high over all the earth.
